It can cause severe irritation if it comes into contact with skin.
On Saturday, Brown posted photos of herself at a hospital in Louisiana where she hoped to get help.
The visit failed to solve the problem.
"This is really about to be a long process," she wrote on Instagram.
Gorilla Glue said in a statement posted on Twitter that it was "very sorry to hear about the unfortunate incident."
"This is a unique situation because this product is not indicated for use in or on hair as it is considered permanent," the statement added.
Brown started a fundraising campaign on GoFundMe to cover the medical costs of her treatment and had already raised more than $15,000 by Tuesday.



